    "summary": "Illustrates a data flow architecture combining frontend validation, state management, and dual storage using Firebase for real-time sync and Blockchain for",
    "whatItShows": "This diagram illustrates a robust data flow architecture starting with user input, followed by frontend validation. Valid data proceeds to state management, which then dispatches data to two distinct storage mechanisms: Firebase Storage for real-time synchronization and Blockchain Storage for immutable record-keeping. Both paths converge to trigger UI updates, ultimately providing user feedback.",
    "whenToUse": "Ideal for applications requiring both real-time data access and immutable, verifiable transaction logs, such as supply chain management, financial applications, or decentralized applications (dApps) where data integrity and auditability are crucial alongside responsive user interfaces.",
    "howToAdapt": "This architecture can be adapted by integrating additional data processing steps (e.g., server-side validation, data transformation) before storage. Other real-time databases (e.g., MongoDB Atlas, AWS DynamoDB) or different blockchain platforms (e.g., Ethereum, Hyperledger Fabric) could replace Firebase and the generic Blockchain. The UI update mechanism could be enhanced with specific notification services or complex state management libraries.",
